    <h1>How to Create the Perfect Knowledge Base for Your AI Voice Agent</h1>

    <p>
      An AI voice agent is only as good as the information you give it.
      A well-designed <strong>knowledge base</strong> makes the agent sound natural,
      reliable and aligned with your business. A poorly structured one
      causes confusion, incorrect answers or unnecessary transfers to a human.
    </p>

    <p>
      In this guide you‚Äôll learn the recommended structure, examples by industry
      and the most common mistakes to avoid.
    </p>

    <h2>Why the Knowledge Base Matters</h2>

    <p>
      The knowledge base is where your AI learns:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>how your business works,</li>
      <li>what you offer,</li>
      <li>your prices, schedules and policies,</li>
      <li>frequently asked questions,</li>
      <li>and how to respond in your tone of voice.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      A good structure improves accuracy and reduces hallucinations.
    </p>

    <h2>Recommended Structure</h2>

    <p>Use this exact structure to keep the agent focused and consistent:</p>

    <h3>1. Business Overview</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>What the business does.</li>
      <li>Who it's for.</li>
      <li>Core services/product categories.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. Hours and Location</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Opening hours.</li>
      <li>Address and how to get there.</li>
      <li>Parking or access details.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Services and Prices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Each service with a clear, short description.</li>
      <li>Price or price range.</li>
      <li>Duration (for clinics, salons, fitness studios, etc.).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4. Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
    <p>Typical questions the agent must answer correctly:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>‚ÄúWhat does this treatment include?‚Äù</li>
      <li>‚ÄúHow long does it take?‚Äù</li>
      <li>‚ÄúDo I need preparation?‚Äù</li>
      <li>‚ÄúIs it painful?‚Äù</li>
      <li>‚ÄúWhat payment methods do you accept?‚Äù</li>
      <li>‚ÄúAre you open on weekends?‚Äù</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. Policies & Instructions</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Cancellation policy.</li>
      <li>Rescheduling rules.</li>
      <li>Preparation instructions.</li>
      <li>Arrival guidelines for first-time clients.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>6. How the Agent Should Communicate</h3>
    <p>
      Define the tone and style:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Friendly and empathetic.</li>
      <li>Short and direct answers.</li>
      <li>Never guess ‚Äî only respond using this knowledge base.</li>
      <li>Offer to transfer when unsure.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Examples by Industry</h2>

    <h3>üè• Clinics (Nubimed or Google Calendar)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>List of treatments with duration.</li>
      <li>Which doctor performs which service.</li>
      <li>Preparation guidelines.</li>
      <li>How to book, move or cancel appointments.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>üè° Real Estate Agencies</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Active listings and key details (typologies, prices, location).</li>
      <li>Promotions, new developments and neighborhoods.</li>
      <li>Buyer qualification: budget, bedrooms, area.</li>
      <li>Process to book a property visit.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>üõí E-commerce / Online Stores</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Shipping policy and delivery times.</li>
      <li>Return and refund instructions.</li>
      <li>Product categories and FAQs.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>üîß Services (gyms, salons, workshops‚Ä¶)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Membership options.</li>
      <li>Service descriptions.</li>
      <li>Opening hours.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Writing long paragraphs (keep answers short).</li>
      <li>Mixing different topics into one block.</li>
      <li>Forgetting prices or durations.</li>
      <li>Using vague descriptions.</li>
      <li>Letting the agent improvise (never do this).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>

    <p>
      A well-structured knowledge base makes your AI voice agent faster,
      more accurate and more natural in conversation.  
      It‚Äôs the easiest way to reduce errors, improve customer experience
